<p><i><b>Youth in Revolt: The Journals of Nick Twisp</b></i> is a <a href="1993_in_literature" title="1993 in literature">1993</a> <a href="Epistolary_novel" title="Epistolary novel">epistolary novel</a> by <a href="../C._D._Payne" title="C. D. Payne">C. D. Payne</a>. The story is told in a <a href="Picaresque" title="Picaresque" class="mw-redirect">picaresque</a> fashion and makes heavy use of <a href="Black_humor" title="Black humor" class="mw-redirect">black humor</a> and <a href="Camp_(style)" title="Camp (style)">camp</a>. The book contains parts one through three of a six-part series (the three sequential parts were published as three separate books).</p>
